==Abstract==

This IIP defines scripts and transaction structures for Hash Time-Locked Contracts (HTLCs), adapted for ML-DSA-87 signatures. HTLCs are the fundamental building block for Lightning Network and atomic swaps.

==Motivation==

HTLCs enable trustless conditional payments:
* Payment succeeds: Recipient reveals preimage to claim funds
* Payment fails: Sender reclaims funds after timeout

Applications:
* Lightning Network payment channels
* Cross-chain atomic swaps
* Trustless escrow
* Multi-hop payments

==Specification==

===Payment Hash===

<pre>
payment_hash = SHA3_256(preimage)
</pre>

Where preimage is a random 32-byte value generated by the recipient.

===Offered HTLC Script===

When offering an HTLC (sender's perspective):

<pre>
# Revocation path
OP_DUP OP_HASH160 <revocation_pubkey_hash> OP_EQUAL
OP_IF
    OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
OP_ELSE
    <remote_htlc_pubkey> OP_SWAP OP_SIZE 32 OP_EQUAL
    OP_NOTIF
        # Timeout path (local reclaims)
        OP_DROP 2 OP_SWAP <local_htlc_pubkey> 2 OP_CHECKMULTISIG
    OP_ELSE
        # Success path (remote claims with preimage)
        OP_SHA256 <payment_hash> OP_EQUALVERIFY
        OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
    OP_ENDIF
OP_ENDIF
</pre>

===Received HTLC Script===

When receiving an HTLC (recipient's perspective):

<pre>
# Revocation path
OP_DUP OP_HASH160 <revocation_pubkey_hash> OP_EQUAL
OP_IF
    OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
OP_ELSE
    <remote_htlc_pubkey> OP_SWAP OP_SIZE 32 OP_EQUAL
    OP_IF
        # Success path (local claims with preimage)
        OP_SHA256 <payment_hash> OP_EQUALVERIFY
        2 OP_SWAP <local_htlc_pubkey> 2 OP_CHECKMULTISIG
    OP_ELSE
        # Timeout path (remote reclaims after CLTV)
        OP_DROP <cltv_expiry> OP_CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY OP_DROP
        OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
    OP_ENDIF
OP_ENDIF
</pre>

===Spending Paths===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Path !! Condition !! Used When
|-
| Success || Preimage revealed || Payment completed
|-
| Timeout || CLTV expired || Payment failed/expired
|-
| Revocation || Old state broadcast || Breach remedy
|}

===INTcoin Adaptations===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Aspect !! BIP 199 !! IIP-42
|-
| Hash function || SHA256 || SHA3-256
|-
| Signature opcode || OP_CHECKSIG || OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
|-
| Signature size || ~72 bytes || 4,627 bytes
|-
| Malleability || Requires SegWit || Inherently non-malleable
|}

==Security Considerations==

* Preimages MUST be generated using CSPRNG
* Preimages MUST be kept secret until payment completion
* CLTV expiry must account for block propagation and path length

